We thought he would soar till he grew •• dy, his brains turn'd, and so speaks Nonsense;
and let it come out; Light, he tells us, is immediate though it comes thro' a Medium •
i. e. its immediate, though it be mediate: but let that pass Whereas he cites Plato (who is with him little inferiour to Moses) to prove that It is man's Inselitity to converse with Images of things; we accept not the Testimony; for Man was made to Converse with the Images of things, and shall so Converse for ever in his perfect state of glory; this being the nature of his understanding, to receive the Knowledge of things by taking in the Images.
